"The European Rights Retention Community of Practice (CoP) continues to bring together experts and practitioners from across Europe to exchange experiences, learn from one another, and advance rights retention strategies.

At this 10th meeting, we are pleased to welcome Ana Lazarova (Digital Republic, Bulgaria), Lionel Maurel (CNRS Sciences humaines &amp; sociales, France) and Sam Moore (University of Cambridge, UK), who will share their perspectives on how open science and rights retention support academic freedom. Beyond the presentations, this meeting offers a space for community members to actively participate by sharing experiences, discussing challenges, and exploring practical solutions together. &nbsp;

If you work at an academic institution, are a funder, or an Open Science policymaker, please join us and contribute to the conversation."

